Know the Types of Tests<br />
Drug tests for marijuana can vary. The most common ones include urine, blood, saliva, and hair follicle tests. Keep in mind that each of these tests has a different detection window.<br />
For instance, urine tests can detect marijuana 3-30 days after use, depending on frequency and quantity of use, while hair &#8230;</p>
